24:43.000 --> 24:46.500
IF WE JUST FORGET
THIS EVER HAPPENED.

25:08.800 --> 25:11.300
FOUR, FIVE, SIX.

25:11.800 --> 25:13.100
FINAL TALLY--

25:13.100 --> 25:14.500
GIO--SIX,

25:14.500 --> 25:16.800
HENRY--SEVEN.

25:16.800 --> 25:18.100
YOU WIN. YAY, HENRY.

25:18.100 --> 25:19.500
OH, YEAH. SEVEN NUMBERS.

25:19.500 --> 25:20.200
WHO'S THE MAN?

25:20.200 --> 25:22.100
USUALLY NOT THE GUY
WHO SAYS, "WHO'S THE MAN?"

25:22.100 --> 25:23.500
OH, AND LOOK, 

25:23.500 --> 25:26.500
SUZIE MADE HER ZEROES 
INTO LITTLE BOOBS.

25:26.500 --> 25:28.200
SHE'S A KEEPER.

25:28.800 --> 25:30.200
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA,
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

25:30.200 --> 25:31.200
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

25:31.200 --> 25:32.900
I'M THROWING THEM AWAY.GIO... 

25:32.900 --> 25:34.600
THIS WAS RESEARCH,
NOT FOR REAL.

25:34.600 --> 25:37.400
FORGET RESEARCH.
I EARNED THESE.

25:37.400 --> 25:40.300
I TOLD THAT GIRL OVER THERE
THAT I'M GOING TO IRAQ NEXT WEEK.

25:41.300 --> 25:42.700
GOTTA STRIKE NOW.

25:43.500 --> 25:44.600
CLASSY.

25:44.800 --> 25:46.800
WELL.
WHAT'D YOU THINK?

25:46.800 --> 25:47.900
I WAS PRETTY GOOD
OUT THERE, HUH?

25:47.900 --> 25:49.000
OOH, CONGRATULATIONS, HENRY.

25:49.000 --> 25:51.500
YOU MANAGED TO SET BACK
THE FEMINIST MOVEMENT 50 YEARS.

25:51.500 --> 25:53.100
HEY, IT WASN'T ME.
IT'S THAT BO.

25:53.100 --> 25:54.500
YOU'RE JUST MAD
BECAUSE IT WORKED.

25:54.500 --> 25:56.400
I'M UPSET ABOUT LOT
OF THINGS, HENRY. 

25:56.400 --> 25:57.900
LET'S JUST GO.

26:02.200 --> 26:04.800
I JUST CAN'T BELIEVE
THIS PHIL ROTH GUY WAS RIGHT.

26:05.100 --> 26:08.100
THESE POOR WOMEN,THEY'RE BEING PLAYED
AND THEY DON'T EVEN KNOW IT.

26:08.100 --> 26:09.000
AY, PLEASE, BETTY. 

26:09.000 --> 26:11.000
THEY KNOW
EXACTLY WHAT THEY'RE DOING.

26:11.000 --> 26:12.400
THEY JUST DON'T WANT
THE GUYS TO KNOW IT.

26:12.400 --> 26:13.900
THAT WAY THEY HAVE
ALL THE POWER.

26:14.600 --> 26:15.900
IT'S NOT A BAD BOOK.

26:15.900 --> 26:16.700
YOU READ IT?

26:16.700 --> 26:18.900
I THUMBED THROUGH IT.
PAPI HAS IT NOW.

26:18.900 --> 26:21.500
UGH. AND THE WORLD IS OVER.

26:21.700 --> 26:23.700
BETTY, GUYS NEED
STUFF LIKE THAT BOOK.

26:23.700 --> 26:25.500
IT GIVES THEM THE CONFIDENCE
TO TALK TO GIRLS.

26:25.500 --> 26:27.400
OTHERWISE THEY'D JUST BE
STARING AT OUR BOOBS.

26:27.400 --> 26:28.900
AND NOW THEY INSULT THEM.

26:28.900 --> 26:30.300
AT LEAST THEY'RE TALKING.

26:30.300 --> 26:32.800
SO YOU'RE ACTUALLY SAYING
THAT THIS IS A POSITIVE THING.

26:32.800 --> 26:36.100
I'M JUST SAYING
BE A LITTLE OPEN-MINDED.

26:37.700 --> 26:39.100
OH, NO.
YOU GOTTA GET THAT.

26:40.600 --> 26:41.200
DANIEL.

26:41.200 --> 26:42.600
I'M SORRY TO BOTHER YOU.

26:42.600 --> 26:44.600
I'VE JUST BEEN DRIVING AROUND
FOR HOURS,

26:45.400 --> 26:47.300
AND I DON'T REALLY KNOW
WHERE TO GO RIGHT NOW.

26:47.300 --> 26:50.500
UM, CLEARLY. YOU ARE IN
JACKSON HEIGHTS AT NIGHT, ALONE,

26:50.500 --> 26:52.500
IN A CAR THAT COST MORE
THAN THIS HOUSE.

26:52.500 --> 26:54.300
DANIEL, I'MTEMPTED
TO JUMP YOU.

26:56.100 --> 26:58.800
WHAT? YOU THINK GORGEOUS
JUST HAPPENS?

27:00.900 --> 27:02.700
I'M JUST SO CONFUSED, BETTY.

27:02.700 --> 27:05.300
SO...
IS THIS ABOUT RENEE?

27:06.000 --> 27:07.800
LOOK, I-I KNOW
SHE'S WILHELMINA'S SISTER,

27:07.800 --> 27:10.900
AND... THIS IS WRONG
IN SO MANY WAYS,

27:10.900 --> 27:12.700
BUT I CAN'T STOP
THINKING ABOUT HER.

27:17.800 --> 27:20.400
WELL, THEN MAYBE
YOU SHOULD GO FOR IT.

27:22.000 --> 27:25.300
WHAT? MAYBE I WAS WRONG
ABOUT WHAT I SAID EARLIER.

27:25.300 --> 27:28.600
I MEAN, LOOK AT HILDA.
WE ARE NOTHING ALIKE.

27:28.600 --> 27:30.200
AND YOU AND ALEXIS?

27:31.300 --> 27:33.900
WHO'S TO SAY RENEE
IS ANYTHING LIKE WILHELMINA?

27:35.000 --> 27:37.700
IF YOU REALLY LIKE HER,
THEN GIVE IT A CHANCE.

27:37.700 --> 27:39.400
WHO KNOWS
WHAT IT COULD TURN INTO?

27:50.400 --> 27:52.000
DON'T TOUCH
THE YOGURT, CHRISTINA.

27:52.000 --> 27:53.900
I DON'T EAT BREAKFAST,
BUT I HAVE IT THERE

27:53.900 --> 27:56.300
SO I KNOW
WHAT I'M DEPRIVING MYSELF OF.

27:57.400 --> 27:58.400
GOOD MORNING.

27:58.600 --> 28:00.200
SORRY, I ALREADY AGU
THE YORT.

28:01.100 --> 28:02.400
YOU CAN LICK THE SPOON
IF YOU'D LIKE.

28:02.400 --> 28:03.700
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

28:03.700 --> 28:06.000
MM.
YOUR SISTER.

28:06.300 --> 28:08.900
THAT'S RIGHT.
WE'RE BACK TOGETHER.

28:09.900 --> 28:12.800
WE DID IT ON YOUR COUCH, TOO,
AND YOUR TABLE.

28:12.800 --> 28:16.400
OH, AND ONE MORE PLACE THAT
I'M NOT GONNA TELL YOU ABOUT.

28:16.400 --> 28:17.700
YOU'RE REALLY ENJOYING THIS,
AREN'T YOU?

28:17.700 --> 28:20.200
YOU THINK IT'S TOO EARLY 
TO START PLANNING FAMILY VACATIONS?

28:20.200 --> 28:21.700
YOU'RE A FOOL, DANIEL.

28:21.900 --> 28:24.300
YOU HAVE NO IDEA WHAT YOU'RE
GETTING YOURSELF INTO.

28:25.600 --> 28:28.700
BUT I PROMISE YOU,
YOU'LL REGRET IT.

28:55.200 --> 28:56.900
AH, I JUST FEEL LIKE
I'VE HEARD THAT BEFORE.

28:56.900 --> 28:58.100
THIS IS TOO HARD.

28:58.100 --> 28:59.200
OKAY, OKAY. 

28:59.200 --> 29:00.900
MAYBE WE NEED
TO APPROACH THIS DIFFERENTLY.

29:00.900 --> 29:03.300
IF GENE SIMMONS WERE HERE
RIGHT NOW,

29:03.500 --> 29:06.000
WHAT WOULD YOU SAY TO HIM
FROM YOUR HEART?

29:35.500 --> 29:36.900
I CAN ONLY HOPE

29:37.500 --> 29:40.300
THAT ONE DAY I'LL HAVE
AN ILLEGITIMATE DAUGHTER

29:40.300 --> 29:42.900
WHO'LL SING ME A SONG THAT'S
THAT BEAUTIFUL.

29:43.300 --> 29:44.900
OH, SWEETIE.

29:45.900 --> 29:47.900
OH, I KNOW.

29:51.200 --> 29:53.800
HEY, HAVE YOU TALKED TO MOM?
I'VE BEEN CALLING HER.

29:53.800 --> 29:55.100
NO, I TRIED HER
A COUPLE OF TIMES, TOO.

29:55.100 --> 29:56.300
SHE HASN'T CALLED ME BACK.

29:56.300 --> 29:59.000
OH, GREAT. NOW SHE'S OFF
SULKING SOMEWHERE.

29:59.100 --> 30:00.200
MAYBE WE DID
KIND OF BLOW IT.

30:00.200 --> 30:02.000
I MEAN, SHE'S ALWAYS
BEEN THERE FOR US.

30:02.300 --> 30:04.900
THAT'S TRUE. THINK OF ALL
THE NIGHTS WE WERE SICK.

30:04.900 --> 30:07.400
SHE'D STAY UP ALL NIGHT
TAKING CARE OF US.

30:07.400 --> 30:11.400
YEAH. WAIT, THAT WASN'T MOM.
THAT WAS THE NANNY.

30:11.800 --> 30:14.500
WELL, STILL, IT'S NICE
SHE HIRED SUCH A CARING NANNY.

30:14.700 --> 30:17.200
I'VE GOT NEWS FOR YOU.
SHE WASN'T THAT CARING.

30:17.200 --> 30:19.100
SHE USED TO TIE YOU
TO EACH OTHER

30:19.100 --> 30:20.400
AND GO TO THE MOVIES.

30:21.800 --> 30:23.400
I THOUGHT
THAT WAS A GAME.

30:23.400 --> 30:25.900
MOM, WHY DIDN'T YOU
RETURN OUR CALLS?

30:25.900 --> 30:27.100
BECAUSE I'VE BEEN TOO BUSY

30:27.100 --> 30:30.500
AT THAT STUPID KNITTING CLASS
YOU SIGNED ME UP FOR.

30:30.500 --> 30:31.100
HERE

30:31.100 --> 30:32.400
IT WAS GOING TO BE A SCARF

30:32.400 --> 30:34.000
UNTIL I REALIZED
HOW MUCH I HATED KNITTING.

30:34.000 --> 30:35.700
BUT THE GOOD NEWS--

30:35.700 --> 30:38.700
I FIGURED OUT WHAT I'M GOING
TO DO WITH THE REST OF MY LIFE.

30:39.400 --> 30:40.100
WHAT?

30:40.100 --> 30:41.800
THERE WERE ALL THESE WOMEN
IN THIS CLASS,

30:41.800 --> 30:43.200
AND THEY WERE JUST LIKE ME.

30:43.200 --> 30:46.500
THEIR CHILDREN WERE DONE
WITH THEM, AND THEY WERE BORED.

30:46.500 --> 30:49.100
SO I GOT TO THINKING,
WE'RE NOT DEAD YET.

30:49.100 --> 30:52.200
THERE'S GOT TO BE MORE OUT THERE
THAN KNITTING AND BINGO.

30:52.200 --> 30:57.600
SO... I'M GOING TO START
A MAGAZINE.

30:58.400 --> 30:59.500
A MAGAZINE?

30:59.500 --> 31:01.300
IT'S FOR WOMEN
OF A CERTAIN AGE

31:01.300 --> 31:04.200
WHO AREN'T READY
FOR THAT ICE FLOE.

31:04.500 --> 31:06.700
I'M GOING CALL IT...

31:06.700 --> 31:07.900
"HOT FLASH."

31:10.000 --> 31:10.900
MOM...

31:10.900 --> 31:12.600
I-I THINK IT'S GREAT THAT
YOU'RE TRYING TO KEEP BUSY,

31:12.600 --> 31:15.400
BUT STARTING UP A MAGAZINE
ISN'T THAT SIMPLE.

31:15.400 --> 31:17.300
OH, DARLING, DO YOU THINK
I WAS MARRIED TO YOUR FATHER

31:17.300 --> 31:18.800
FOR ALL THOSE YEARS
WITHOUT LEARNING A THING 

31:18.800 --> 31:20.100
OR TWO ABOUT THIS BUSINESS?

31:20.500 --> 31:23.600
I'M GOING TO NEED AN ASSISTANT,
A FULL-TIME PRODUCTION STAFF,

31:23.600 --> 31:25.800
A SUITE OF OFFICES--
THE SEVENTH FLOOR WILL BE FINE.

31:25.800 --> 31:28.600
-MOM
-AND I'M GOING TO NEED SOME START-UP CAPITAL.

31:29.400 --> 31:33.000
LET'S SEE HOW LONG
$2 MILLION LASTS ME.

31:33.000 --> 31:34.300
MAYBE WE SHOULD
HAVE DINNER FIRST

31:34.300 --> 31:35.300
AND JUST TALK ABOUT THIS.

31:35.300 --> 31:38.700
I'D LOVE TO, KIDS,
BUT I DON'T HAVE TIME.

31:38.700 --> 31:39.900
TOODLES.

31:42.400 --> 31:43.700
-"HOT FLASH."
-"HOT FLASH."

31:44.600 --> 31:46.100
OH, I'D TAP THAT.

31:46.800 --> 31:48.200
HELLO, MR. ROTH.

31:49.000 --> 31:50.400
THANK YOU FOR...

31:50.400 --> 31:52.900
MEETING WITH ME... 
AGAIN.

31:52.900 --> 31:55.100
I'VE SEEN YOUR BOOK
IN ACTION,

31:55.100 --> 31:58.400
AND AS HARD AS THIS IS
FOR ME TO ADMIT,

31:59.000 --> 32:02.200
IT ACTUALLY WORKS...
ON SOME GIRLS.

32:03.300 --> 32:04.500
WOW.

32:05.000 --> 32:07.800
THAT IS REALLY COOL OF YOU
TO ADMIT THAT.

32:07.800 --> 32:10.900
YOU KNOW, SMART GIRLS
USUALLY DON'T GET IT.

32:11.500 --> 32:12.600
RIGHT.
WELL, 

32:12.600 --> 32:15.700
YOU CAN REST ASSURED THAT 
THE ARTICLE WILL BE TOTALLY UNBIASED,

32:15.700 --> 32:18.400
AND YOU SHOULD ALSO KNOW
THAT YOUR CONCERNS

32:18.400 --> 32:21.600
WERE COMPLETELY UNWARRANTED.

32:21.800 --> 32:23.000
WHAT C-CONCERNS?

32:23.000 --> 32:25.200
YOU KNOW, THE ONES
YOU EXPRESSED TO DANIEL

32:25.200 --> 32:28.600
ABOUT ME NOT BEING OPEN-MINDED 
ENOUGH TO WRITE THIS ARTICLE.

32:28.600 --> 32:29.700
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT

32:29.700 --> 32:30.900
'CAUSE I-I NEVER S--
I NEVER SAID THAT.

32:30.900 --> 32:31.700
WHAT?

32:31.700 --> 32:34.100
MNH-MNH.
NO, DANIEL SAID THAT YOU--

32:34.100 --> 32:35.100
UH-OH.

32:36.300 --> 32:38.400
MAYBE YOU'RE NOT SO SMART
AFTER ALL.

32:40.000 --> 32:41.900
SOUNDS LIKE
SOMEBODY GOT PLAYED.

32:46.400 --> 32:48.800
GOOD MORNING, DANIEL.
I GOT YOU A TREAT.

32:48.900 --> 32:50.000
CINNAMON TWIST!

32:50.000 --> 32:51.100
I LOVE CINNAMON TWISTS.

32:51.100 --> 32:52.400
WELL,
YOU'RE NOT GETTING IT.

32:52.700 --> 32:54.300
DO WE ALWAYS
HAVE TO PLAY THESE GAMES

32:54.300 --> 32:55.100
WHEN YOU'RE MAD AT ME?

32:55.100 --> 32:57.300
OH, YOU'RE ONE
TO TALK ABOUT GAMES.

32:57.300 --> 32:59.800
LET'S SEE, YOU TOLD ME
THAT PHIL ROTH SAID

32:59.800 --> 33:03.300
I WAS CLOSED-MINDED,
BUT HE NEVER SAID THAT.

33:03.500 --> 33:05.000
OKAY, YES, YOU'RE RIGHT.

33:05.000 --> 33:07.100
CAN I PLEASE HAVE
THE CINNAMON TWIST?

33:07.200 --> 33:08.600
NO. IS THAT IT?
THAT'S ALL?

33:08.600 --> 33:10.800
YOU'RE NOT EVEN GONNA TRY
TO DENY IT?

33:10.800 --> 33:12.400
LOOK, I SAID IT BECAUSE I
COULDN'T THINK OF ANYTHING ELSE

33:12.400 --> 33:13.700
TO GET YOU
TO WRITE THE ARTICLE.

33:13.700 --> 33:14.900
WHAT?

33:14.900 --> 33:17.100
BETTY, YOU WERE QUITTING
BECAUSE YOU WERE UNCOMFORTABLE.

33:17.300 --> 33:18.600
NOW IF YOU WANT TO BE
A REAL WRITER,

33:18.600 --> 33:21.200
YOU CAN'T ALWAYS WRITE ABOUT
YOUR NEIGHBORHOOD

33:21.200 --> 33:23.200
AND YOUR FAMILY
AND--AND KITTENS.

33:23.200 --> 33:25.200
WELL, WHAT'S WRONG
WITH WRITING ABOUT THAT?

33:25.200 --> 33:28.100
THAT'S WHAT I KNOW.
AND WHO DOESN'T LIKE KITTENS?

33:28.100 --> 33:29.900
THERE'S NOTHING WRONG WITH
WRITING ABOUT WHAT YOU KNOW.

33:29.900 --> 33:32.700
I'M JUST SAYING YOU SHOULD
TRY TO KNOW MORE,

33:32.700 --> 33:34.000
STEP OUTSIDE
YOUR COMFORT ZONE.

33:34.000 --> 33:35.100
AND YOU DID.

33:35.100 --> 33:38.700
BETTY, YOUR ARTICLE--
IT'S GOOD.

33:38.900 --> 33:41.300
REALLY?
YOU LIKED IT?

33:41.300 --> 33:42.100
YEAH.

33:42.100 --> 33:44.100
I'M GETTING PUBLISHED?

33:44.100 --> 33:47.500
ACTUALLY, UH, YOU'RE NOT
GETTING PUBLISHED.

33:47.500 --> 33:48.400
WHY?

33:48.400 --> 33:49.600
ALEXIS PULLED THE STORY.

33:49.600 --> 33:52.400
I GUESS WHEN SHE WAS A GUY
SHE LOVED PHIL ROTH,

33:52.400 --> 33:54.900
AND AS A WOMAN, SHE THINKS
HE'S KIND OF A PIG.

33:54.900 --> 33:57.400
OH! YOU'RE KIDDING ME,
RIGHT?

33:57.400 --> 33:58.500
I'M SORRY.

33:58.800 --> 34:01.500
BUT YOU DID DO
A FANTASTIC JOB.

34:01.500 --> 34:03.000
AND I PROMISE,

34:03.000 --> 34:05.800
THERE'S GONNA BE
OTHER ASSIGNMENTS,BETTER ONES.

34:06.500 --> 34:07.600
ALL RIGHT.

34:07.900 --> 34:09.900
THIS TOTALLY SUCKS.

34:11.400 --> 34:13.100
BUT, DANIEL, THANK YOU

34:14.100 --> 34:15.900
FOR HAVING FAITH IN ME.

34:21.800 --> 34:23.100
THANK YOU.

34:26.800 --> 34:28.699
WHY ARE YOU DOING
LONG DIVISION?

34:29.100 --> 34:30.500
IT CALMS ME.

34:31.500 --> 34:33.500
DO NOT BE NERVOUS 
ABOUT THE BAND TONIGHT.

34:33.500 --> 34:37.000
THERE IS NO WAY THAT AMANDA 
COULD POSSIBLY BE WORSE THAN CLYDE.

34:37.800 --> 34:39.400
I CAN ASK HILDA
TO COME WITH.

34:39.800 --> 34:41.000
OH, AND I CAN CALL GIO.

34:41.000 --> 34:43.000
HE'LL BRING ONE OF THOSE GIRLS
HE MET AT THE BAR.

34:44.400 --> 34:46.100
OH, YOU KNOW,
 I'M GOOD.

34:46.100 --> 34:47.800
I PUT UP A LOT OF POSTERS
IN THE VILLAGE.

34:47.800 --> 34:50.600
YEAH, BUT IF HE BRINGS SOMEONE,
THEN THAT'S 20 EXTRA BUCKS.

34:53.800 --> 34:55.699
HENRY, ARE YOU SERIOUS?

34:56.000 --> 34:58.700
LO, YOU CANNOT BE
SO COMPETITIVE WITH HIM.

34:58.700 --> 34:59.900
I HAVE TO BE.

35:01.100 --> 35:02.200
WHY?

35:02.200 --> 35:04.500
BECAUSE, BETTY,
HE'S ALWAYS AROUND,

35:04.500 --> 35:06.900
AND I TRUST YOU COMPLETELY.

35:06.900 --> 35:08.300
I JUST DON'T TRUST HIM.

35:08.300 --> 35:11.000
SO WHAT, YOU THINK
HE'S GONNA WALK OVER

35:11.000 --> 35:12.500
AND KNOCK ME ON THE HEAD
WITH A CLUB

35:12.500 --> 35:14.000
AND DRAG ME BACK
TO HIS CAVE?

35:14.000 --> 35:15.700
I DO HAVE SOME SAY IN IT.

35:15.700 --> 35:16.900
IT'S JUST HARD.

35:17.600 --> 35:19.400
LOOK, DO YOU REMEMBER
HOW YOU FELT AT THE BAR

35:19.400 --> 35:20.900
WATCHING ME
HIT ON ALL THOSE WOMEN?

35:21.900 --> 35:25.000
THAT'S HOW I FEEL EVERY TIME
I SEE GIO AROUND YOU.

35:25.600 --> 35:28.900
WELL... I HATE
THAT YOU FEEL THAT WAY.

35:29.400 --> 35:31.800
I'M SORRY.
I HATE IT, TOO.

35:34.500 --> 35:37.500
LOOK,I-I DON'T WANT ANYTHING 
TO GET IN THE WAY

35:37.500 --> 35:40.100
OF THE LITTLE TIME
THAT WE HAVE LEFT TOGETHER.

35:40.600 --> 35:42.400
I JUST WON'T
SEE HIM ANYMORE.

35:42.700 --> 35:44.500
NOW I FEEL STUPID.

35:44.800 --> 35:46.900
I KNOW HOW MUCH YOU LOVE
HIS CHICKEN SALAD.

35:46.900 --> 35:49.800
YEAH,
BUT I LOVE YOU MORE.

35:53.700 --> 35:56.300
YOU WILL LEARN HOW TO MAKE
CHICKEN SALAD, THOUGH,WON'T YOU?

35:58.200 --> 35:59.800
OKAY, REMEMBER,
LOOK INTO THE CAMERA,

35:59.800 --> 36:02.200
AVOID YOUR BAD ANGLES,
AND I DID EVERYTHING I COULD,

36:02.200 --> 36:03.500
BUT THIS LIGHTING
IS NOT YOUR FRIEND.

36:03.500 --> 36:04.800
MARC, 
I'M REALLY NERVOUS.

36:04.800 --> 36:07.800
HEY. YOU HAVE NOTHING
TO BE NERVOUS ABOUT.

36:07.800 --> 36:10.000
EXCEPT FOR YOUR VOICE,
YOU'RE A GREAT SINGER.

36:10.600 --> 36:11.900
-READY?
-YEAH.

36:11.900 --> 36:13.800
HELLO,
 BEER HOLE.

36:13.800 --> 36:16.800
ARE YOU READY TO ROCK
AND/OR ROLL?

36:19.000 --> 36:20.100
OKAY, GO.

36:22.900 --> 36:25.000
THIS ONE
GOES OUT TO YOU, DADDY.

36:25.900 --> 36:28.100
IT'S MANDY, BITCH.

36:52.900 --> 36:55.000
EXCUSE ME, MA'AM.
YOU'RE IN MY WAY.

36:56.000 --> 36:59.300
DO YOU MIND?
SHE'S SINGING ABOUT ME.

36:59.300 --> 37:01.600
NO. SHE'S SINGING ABOUT
GENE SIMMONS.

38:00.600 --> 38:01.600
DADDY?

38:02.200 --> 38:03.800
-DAUGHTER?
-AMANDA.

38:03.800 --> 38:05.700
-AMANDA.
-I CAN'BELIEVE YOU CAME.

38:05.700 --> 38:07.100
HOW DID YOU KNOW
WE WERE DOING THIS?

38:07.100 --> 38:09.000
OH, I GOOGLE MYSELF
EVERY MORNING.

38:09.000 --> 38:10.200
ME, TOO.

38:10.300 --> 38:12.900
YOU KNOW, THE DETAIL OF
THAT SONG, IT WAS SPOT-ON.

38:12.900 --> 38:14.600
YOU CAN'T FORGET
A NIGHT LIKE THAT,

38:14.600 --> 38:16.200
OR A WOMAN LIKE FEY.

38:16.200 --> 38:18.800
MAN, CHER WAS SO PISSED OFF.

38:19.500 --> 38:23.400
SO IT'S TRUE.
YOU'RE MY FATHER.

38:24.100 --> 38:27.200
OH, MY GOD.
I FOUND YOU.

38:33.100 --> 38:34.300
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT,

38:34.300 --> 38:36.800
LET'S GET OUTTA HERE.
MAYBE WE'LL CATCH UP?

38:36.800 --> 38:39.000
I KNOW WE BOTH HAVE
SOME QUESTIONS. COME ON.

38:39.000 --> 38:39.800
OKAY

